<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1904-06-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1904-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="510" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d510">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gummeré</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate-General</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1904-06-23"><hi rend="italic">June 23,
                                1904</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Gummeré acknowledges receipt of Department’s instructions yesterday,
                            and states that, while acting in close touch with the British minister,
                            he has not entertained any idea of departing from his present <pb facs="0592" n="504" xml:id="pg_504"/> attitude without having first
                            received positive instructions from the Department. He reports that
                            Shereef left for Zellal’s village very early this morning with money and
                            prisoners.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>